The obvious surface-level issues are mostly “unsafe ERC20 assumptions” and owner misconfiguration, but I’m checking whether there are stronger protocol-native bugs before I settle on those. Right now the main candidates are around irreversible debt burn in `collect` paths, fee parameter values that can brick newly created pools, and whether limit-order accounting can be forced into a stale or double-counted state.
